subSubSection.paragraph:
Ocular plate (
Fig. 3B, C
). Ocelli 8 + 8, in black pigmented eyepatch. PAO round with 6-8 vesicles, arranged in a circle, approximately the same size as an ocellus.

Mouthparts (
Fig. 4A, B
). Buccal cone truncated. Mandibles absent. Maxilla head typical of the genus, globular, with five strong, apically rounded teeth and parallel striations proximally, a sixth one, very reduced, sometimes present basally. Labium with subequal chaetae.A, B, C, D, E, F, f, G and 5 lateral ones (a, b, c, d, e); rooted papillate chaeta L present; no x-papilla seen.
